Arcane Weapon		KEY:Arcane Weapon ~ Magus		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural			DEFINE:MagusArcaneWeaponLVL|0	DEFINE:MagusArcaneWeaponBonus|0	DESC:You can imbue a melee weapon with powerful abilities. When you prepare your spells, you can also spend a portion of this time bonding with a single melee weapon. This grants the weapon a +%1 enhancement bonus. These bonuses can be added to the weapon, stacking with existing weapon enhancement to a maximum of +5, or they can be used be used to add any of the following weapon properties: dancing, flaming, flaming burst, frost, icy burst, keen, shock, shocking burst, speed, or vorpal. Adding these properties consumes an amount of bonus equal to the property's cost. These properties are added to any the weapon already has, but duplicates do not stack. If the weapon is not magical, at least a +1 enhancement bonus must be added before any other properties can be added. These bonuses and properties are decided when the weapon is bonded and cannot be changed until the next time the magus prepares spells. These bonuses do not function if the weapon is wielded by anyone other than the magus. Bonding with a weapon in this way is not without danger. A magus that is bonded to a weapon must have the weapon in hand to cast spells from the magus spell list; otherwise he must make a concentration check to cast such spells. The DC of this check is equal to 20 + the spell's level.|MagusArcaneWeaponBonus																																																																																																			BONUS:VAR|MagusArcaneWeaponBonus|min(MagusArcaneWeaponLVL/4,20)	SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Fighter Training		KEY:Fighter Training ~ Magus		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary			DEFINE:MagusFighterTrainingLVL|0						DESC:You count 1/2 your total magus level as your fighter level for the purpose of qualifying for feats. If you have levels in fighter, these levels stack.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Fighter Level Advanced Feat Tracker|Weapon Specialization Qualify|Greater Shield Focus Qualify|Greater Weapon Focus Qualify|Spellbreaker Qualify|Greater Weapon Specialization Qualify|Penetrating Strike Qualify|Critical Mastery Qualify|Greater Penetrating Strike Qualify									BONUS:VAR|FighterLVL|MagusFighterTrainingLVL/2				SOURCEPAGE:p.385
Counterstrike		KEY:Counterstrike ~ Magus		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary														DESC:Whenever an enemy within your reach successfully casts a spell defensively, that enemy provokes an attack of opportunity from you after the spell is complete. This attack of opportunity cannot disrupt the spell.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Weapon Bond			KEY:Weapon Bond ~ Magus			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural														DESC:If you are bonded to a weapon through the arcane weapon class feature, you can call that weapon to your hand as a free action once per round. The weapon appears in your hand instantly, even if it is in the possession of another creature or on another plane of existence. This ability does not function in areas that prevent or block teleportation magic or planar travel. Alternatively, you can teleport to the nearest open square to your bonded weapon, as if using Greater Teleport, except that you cannot bring any other creatures with you. In addition, if the weapon is not in your possession, you can scry on it at will and any creature in possession of the item takes a -8 penalty on its saving throw to resist this scrying.																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.5

