Concentrate				KEY:Concentrate ~ Magus Arcana			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.MagusArcana											DESC:You can reroll any concentration check you have just made with a +4 bonus. You must use this ability after the roll is made, but before it is determined if the roll is a success. You must take the second roll, even if it is worse. You can use this ability once per day.																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Critical Strike			KEY:Concentrate ~ Magus Arcana			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural.MagusArcana	PREVARGTEQ:MagusArcanaLVL,12						DESC:Whenever you score a critical hit with a melee weapon, you may cast a spell with a range of touch as a swift action, then make a touch attack against the target of the critical hit as a free action. You can use this ability once per day.																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Dispelling Strike			KEY:Dispelling Strike ~ Magus Arcana		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural.MagusArcana	PREVARGTEQ:MagusArcanaLVL,9						DESC:You can sacrifice one of your prepared magus spells as a swift action to imbue your weapon with a special aura. If the weapon strikes a creature within the next minute, that creature is the subject of a targeted Dispel Magic using the your level as the caster level, except that this effect cannot dispel a spell of a level higher than that sacrificed spell (treat higher-level spells as if they do not exist and apply the dispel attempt to the remaining spells with the highest caster level). Once the strike is made, the aura dissipates, even if the dispel attempt is unsuccessful.																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Empowered Magic			KEY:Empowered Magic ~ Magus Arcana			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural.MagusArcana	PREVARGTEQ:MagusArcanaLVL,6						DESC:You can cast one spell per day as if it were modified by the Empower Spell feat. This does not increase the casting time or the level of the spell.																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.4
